<HEADLINE>
<P>
ON THE COVER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Turning the TV dial in search of fresh prime-time fare? 
</P>
<P>
Try tuning in "FM," a new NBC sitcom starring Robert Hays as the program 
director and disc jockey at a listener-supported radio station in Washington. 
The half-hour MTM Enterprises series takes the airwaves for a five-week tryout 
starting Thursday at 9:30 p.m. on Channels 4, 36 and 39 before moving to its 
regular Wednesday night time slot at 9:30 p.m. on Aug. 23. 
</P>
<P>
Created by Emmy winner Allan Burns ("The Mary Tyler Moore Show," "Lou Grant") 
and Dan Wilcox, the cast of "FM" includes Patricia Richardson, Leo Geter and 
DeLane Mathews, co-stars of the defunct CBS comedy, "Eisenhower and Lutz." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, COLOR, Robert Hays, Patricia Richardson, Leo Geter and DeLane Mathews 
Steve Fontanini / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
