</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The high court in the Maldives sentenced a Sri Lanka-based Maldivian 
businessman to death for leading a failed coup in the Indian Ocean archipelago, 
the Maldivian government announced. Seventy-five people, including 68 Sri 
Lankan Tamil mercenaries, were convicted of participating in the Nov. 3, 1988 
coup attempt. Sixteen people -- four Maldivians and 12 Sri Lankans -- were 
given death sentences. The others received prison terms ranging from nine to 38 
years. The court found businessman Abdullah Luthufi guilty of organizing the 
attempt to overthrow President Maumoon Abdul Gayoom. The attempt was crushed by 
Indian paratroopers after Gayoom requested help. 
