<HEADLINE>
<P>
OUTTAKES: WEIGHTY MATTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Pat H. Broeske 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The casting call was for a woman of 5-foot-4, size 22, about 230-260 pounds -- 
a Roseanne Barr body double for "She Devil." There was a catch: She had to be 
nude. 
</P>
<P>
Plus Models Ltd. of NYC -- which specializes in larger-size models -- took the 
call from the film's production office. The Orion comedy, which just wrapped in 
Gotham, stars Meryl Streep as a romance novelist who comes between clumsy 
housewife Barr and hubby, Ed Begley Jr. -- leading Barr to plot revenge. 
</P>
<P>
"But we couldn't find any girls who were interested (or the right size)," said 
Plus Models prez Pat Swift. 
</P>
<P>
"Most of our girls start at 5-foot-8 1/2. Then there's the fact they wanted the 
girl to pose nude. You know, the bigger a girl gets, the more reluctant she 
tends to be about taking her clothes off." 
</P>
<P>
Swift also said the potential pay was well below usual for a day's 
nude/semi-nude work -- an initial offer of $125, later raised to $175. 
</P>
<P>
We aren't sure if a size 22 body double was ever found, or filmed. At press 
time, calls to the film's production office, Orion and Barr's publicist had not 
been returned. Pat H. Broeske 
</P>
</TEXT>
