<HEADLINE>
<P>
OSSO BUCO; 
</P>
<P>
WHO WOULD HAVE THOUGHT THAT THIS WOULD TURN OUT TO BE ONE OF THE TRENDIEST 
DISHES OF THE '80S? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kathie Jenkins 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Buon Gusto, 3110 Main St., Santa Monica. (213) 452-4288. Style: Charming 
neighborhood spot with a mainstream modern L.A.-Italian menu. Setting: 
Pilasters, posters, paintings and a precious patio. Recommended: Osso buco, 
$13. 
</P>
<P>
Chapo, 7661 Melrose Ave., Los Angeles. (213) 655-2924. Style: Tip your hat to 
this quirky Franco-Mediterranean spot. Setting: Sleek and sassy. Recommended: 
Osso buco, $13.50. 
</P>
<P>
Da Pasquale, 9749 Santa Monica Blvd., Beverly Hills. (213) 859-3884. Style: 
Beverly Hills' best cheap restaurant. Setting: Tight-squeeze coffee shop. 
Recommended: Osso buco, $9.50. 
</P>
<P>
