<P>
ANTI-DRUG CRUSADER EULOGIZED AT MASS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Slain anti-drug crusader Maria Hernandez was eulogized at a Mass attended by 
300 mourners in New York, including Mayor Edward I. Koch. There was heavy 
security to prevent further violence against her family. Hernandez, 34, a 
mother of three who with her husband had fought to force drug dealers out of 
her Brooklyn neighborhood, was shot to death last week, possibly in retaliation 
for her anti-drug efforts. During a 70-minute Mass in Spanish and English at 
St. John the Baptist Catholic Church, the Rev. Charles Plock praised the 
woman's efforts to transform her neighborhood into a place where there would be 
"no mourning, no tears, no fear. She labored and she struggled and she fought. 
She organized people to make her community reflect this new heaven and this new 
Earth," Plock said. "Maria gave her life because she was not afraid to speak 
the truth." 
</P>
