<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE NATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the third major Free World rocket launch in five days, the 126-foot, 
$30-million Delta 2, equipped with nine strap-on solid-fuel boosters, was 
scheduled for takeoff from the Cape Canaveral Air Force Station in Florida 
early today. Atop the slender blue-and-white rocket inside a protective nose 
cone was the third of 21 new $65-million Global Positioning System navigation 
satellites designed to tell military units their locations to within 53 feet 
anywhere in the world. Heavy thunderstorms rolled through the cape and an Air 
Force spokeswoman said there was a 20% chance of the weather delaying the 
launch. 
