</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Al Unser Jr. won the finale of the International Race of Champions at Watkins 
Glen, N.Y., but Terry Labonte's third-place finish gave him the championship of 
the four-race international road circuit all-star series for 1989. 
</P>
<P>
Labonte took the $200,000 first prize in the $806,500 series and wound up with 
72 points. Unser finished second with 60 points and $93,000 as he tied former 
stock car champion Cale Yarborough for the most career IROC victories with 
five. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
