<HEADLINE>
<P>
RETURN THE TAX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Should a citizen become involved in a tax dispute with the government and lose 
his case, that person must post the amount of the monetary judgment, as a bond, 
to appeal his case to a higher court. 
</P>
<P>
The County of San Diego lost its claim of a half-percent sales tax when 
Superior Court Judge Gordon Burkhart ruled it illegal March 24. 
</P>
<P>
Why doesn't the County of San Diego have to return the half-percent sales tax 
it already collected to the citizens who paid it before the county can be 
allowed to appeal the case to a higher court? 
</P>
<P>
WALTER P. BLOOMENBECK 
</P>
<P>
Lilac 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA081389-0159 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 94384 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
August 13, 1989, Sunday, San Diego County Edition 
