<P>
NORWAY OIL SLICK BEGINS TO BREAK UP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
OSLO, Norway 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 38-square-mile oil slick around Norway's huge North Sea Statfjord field has 
begun to break up and officials said Friday there appeared to be little danger 
of environmental damage. 
</P>
