<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPORTS ET CETERA: DEL MAR TO HONOR BILL SHOEMAKER ON SEPT. 10 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bill Shoemaker, thoroughbred horse racing's all-time winningest jockey with 
more than 8,800 victories, will be given a special day at the Del Mar on Sept. 
10 as part of his farewell tour. 
</P>
<P>
Shoemaker, who will turn 58 on Aug. 19, announced last year he is retiring in 
February at Santa Anita, and he is touring race tracks around the world. 
</P>
<P>
General Manager Joseph Harper said Shoemaker will be honored with a ceremony. 
The $100,000 Budweiser Breeders' Cup stakes will be the featured race. 
</P>
<P>
BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
Dave Kirksey, Christian Heritage College's all-time men's basketball leader in 
rebounding (471) and shooting percentage (64.9), will return next season as a 
graduate assistant, according to Swen Nater, the school's athletic director. 
</P>
<P>
DIVING 
</P>
<P>
Kristen Walls, a Monte Vista graduate who will attend UCLA, finished seventh in 
the girls' 16-18 platform diving competition at the Junior Olympic national 
championships at The Woodlands, Tex. Walls leaves today for Raleigh-Durham, 
N.C., where she will compete on the one-meter board at the senior national 
outdoor competition. 
</P>
